My seven year old and four year old love this series. They can quote from it and even play Fanboy Chum Chum roles play from time to time. I myself find the series quite enjoyable as well. There's lots of reference to pop culture (star wars, harry potter and the like) and lots of satire of everyday life. If you're expecting something serious with character development (as many on the lower reviews seem to lament on) then you're looking in the wrong place, this is just wacky fun although there are many layers if you're prepared to give it a chance.
